The President spoke with FEMA Administrator Craig Fugate and Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism Lisa Monaco to receive an update on the impacts of Hurricane Matthew and ongoing federal response efforts. Recovery efforts are underway in Florida, Georgia, and South Carolina, while response efforts continue in North Carolina. Administrator Fugate emphasized that continued flooding in the Carolinas will create dangerous conditions in the coming days. The President stressed the need for all necessary federal resources to be directed to the impacted states and urged those in the potential path of flooding to listen to local officials. The President expressed his condolences for those who lost their lives and his thoughts and prayers for all those affected. He will continue to be briefed on the response to Hurricane Matthew throughout the week.